2026-04-21 02:46:09 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['ctrl1_green_led', 'ctrl2_green_led', 'ctrl3_green_led', 'ctrl4_green_led', 'ctrl5_green_led', 'ctrl6_green_led', 'ctrl7_green_led', 'ctrl8_green_led'] hypothesis_explanation="All of the control module indicator LEDs (ctrl1_green_led through ctrl8_green_led) are physically missing from their holders. In this circuit, each module's LED and its series resistor are wired in parallel to the main power line and across the open/closed switch path. With all switches closed, these missing LEDs (and their associated open circuits) create a gap in the parallel branches, causing an open circuit for the current in each module. This condition prevents the current from reaching the load, so the lamp does not light. Since the wiring was confirmed to be correct, the root cause is the absence of these LEDs, which interrupts the continuity required for the circuit to function."
